 Linux), highly customizable using the Python language. It reads and writes to many open file formats such as STEP, IGES, STL, SVG, DXF, OBJ, IFC, DAE and many others, making it possible to seamlessly integrate it into your workflow. FreeCAD includes a modern Finite Element Analysis (FEA) tools, experimental CFD, BIM, Geodata workbenches, a Path (CNC) workbench, a robot simulation module that allows you to study robot movements and many more, and a rich collection of plugins and macros installable directly from within the applicationgversionn20241003stableldownload_urlxühttps://github.com/realthunder/FreeCAD/releases/download/20241003stable/FreeCAD-Link-Stable-Linux-x86_64-py3.11-20241003.AppImagedsizei849.93 MBhsrc_urlsüx/https://github.com/realthunder/FreeCAD/releaseshweb_urlsüxhttps://github.com/realthunderhprovideslfreecad-asm3glicenseühLGPL-2.1kmaintainersx9AppImage (https://github.com/AppImage/appimage.github.io)enotesćx:[EXTERNAL] (This is an unofficial, third-party repository)xI[UNTRUSTED] (We CAN NOT guarantee the authenticity, validity or security)x2This data was autogenerated & is likely inaccuratex/Data used: https://appimage.github.io/feed.jsonx;Provided by: https://github.com/AppImage/appimage.github.ioxNLearn More: https://docs.pkgforge.dev/repositories/external/appimage.github.iox;Please create an Issue or send a PR for an official Package«cpkgqfreecad2.appimagehpkg_namehfreecad2fpkg_idx#appimage.github.io.FreeCAD2.FreeCADdiconxģhttps://raw.githubusercontent.com/AppImage/appimage.github.io/refs/heads/master/database/icons/FreeCAD2/icons/64x64/freecad_conda.pngkdescriptionyĆFreeCAD is a parametric 3D modeler. Parametric modeling allows you to easily modify your design by going back into your model history and changing its parameters. FreeCAD is open source (LGPL license) and completely modular, allowing for very advanced extension and customization. FreeCAD is multiplatfom, and reads and writes many open file formats such as STEP, IGES, STL and othe